# Stripe Integration Rules

## Positive Directives

- Always use Stripe Connect with `payment_intent_data.transfer_data.destination` for organizer payouts
- Always include `application_fee_amount` in checkout sessions to capture the platform fee
- Use the `calculatePlatformFee()` helper from `@/lib/stripe` for consistent fee calculation
- Store the Stripe session ID on the Order model for reconciliation
- Always verify webhook signatures using `stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()`
- Use `metadata` on Stripe checkout sessions to pass the `orderId` for webhook reconciliation
- Handle idempotency: check if an order is already COMPLETED before processing the webhook again
- All Stripe API calls must happen server-side only (Server Actions or API routes)

## Negative Rules

- NEVER expose the Stripe secret key to client components
- NEVER process payments without verifying the webhook signature
- NEVER hardcode the platform fee percentage - always read from `STRIPE_PLATFORM_FEE_PERCENT` env var
- NEVER create a checkout session without a connected Stripe account destination
- NEVER skip error handling on Stripe API calls

## Verification Steps

- Confirm the webhook route at `/api/webhooks/stripe` correctly verifies signatures
- Confirm `application_fee_amount` and `transfer_data.destination` are present in every checkout session
- Test the full flow: create checkout -> complete payment -> webhook fires -> order marked COMPLETED -> tickets generated
